1. First copy the files "My_Alarm.c", "errors.h" and "make" into your
   own directory.

2. To compile our program use the following command (our make file):

      make

3. Type "a.out" to run the executable code.

4. At the prompt "alarm>", type in the number of seconds at which
   the alarm should expire, followed by the text of the message.
   For example:

   alarm> 2 Good Morning!

  (To exit from the program, type Ctrl-d or Ctrl-c)